lead_paragraph: Clemson running back Wayne Gallman said Monday that the hit by North Carolina State defensive back Dravious Wright that knocked him out of the game on Oct. 15 was "dirty" and he wanted a teammate to retaliate.

headline.print_headline: Clemson RB Gallman Says Hit by NC State's Wright Was 'Dirty'
